Citation.sAbstract: Surface tensions of binary mixtures of N-methyldiethanolamine and triethanolamine with ethanol were  determined at (15 to 40) deg C over the entire range of concentrations to analyze the influence of both variables.  The Redlich Kister equation was employed to fit surface tension deviation obtained from experimental  values.
Citation.sTitle: Surface Tension of Binary Mixtures of N-Methyldiethanolamine and Triethanolamine with Ethanol
